{"title_page": "Israel Pliner", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2014}}\n[[File:Izrail Pliner NKVD.jpg|alt=Izrail Pliner|thumb|238x238px|Izrail Pliner]]\n'''Israel Pliner''' ({{lang-ru|\u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u044c \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041f\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440}}, '''Izrail Izrailevich Pliner''') (1896&ndash;1939) was a Soviet communist and high functionary of the [[Soviet secret police]] . Notable posts include deputy chief of [[GULAG|GULAGS]]<ref>{{Cite book|last=Congdon|first=Lee|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=oK68DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT169&dq=Israel+Pliner&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=Israel%20Pliner&f=false|title=Solzhenitsyn: The Historical-Spiritual Destinies of Russia and the West|date=2017-09-15|publisher=Cornell University Press|isbn=978-1-60909-224-5|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Baberowski|first=J\u00f6rg|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=DqFTDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT148&dq=Israel+Pliner&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=Israel%20Pliner&f=false|title=Scorched Earth: Stalin's Reign of Terror|date=2016-11-22|publisher=Yale University Press|isbn=978-0-300-22057-5|language=en}}</ref> in (1935-1937) and  (1937-1938). \n\nHe was one of the main collaborators of [[Nikolai Yezhov]], head of the [[NKVD]] in the years 1936\u20131938, and collaborator of other organizers of the [[Great Purge|Great Terror in the USSR]]. \n\nOn August 16, 1937, he became the head of the board of the communist concentration camps GULAG [[NKVD]] five days after the beginning of [[Polish Operation of the NKVD]]. According to NKVD documents, 139,835 Poles who were citizens of the USSR were convicted in 1937. Of this number, 111 091 Poles were directly killed, and 28 744 Poles were sent to communist [[Gulag|GULAG]] concentration camps.\n\nIn 1937, he directed the deportation of 172,000 Korean citizens of the USSR from the Soviet Far East to Central Asia (to Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan).\n\nHe was arrested in 1938 and executed in 1939.<ref>[http://hrono.ru/biograf/bio_p/plinerii.php \"\u041f\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440 \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u044c \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447\"] at hrono.ru, citing books:\n\n*\u0417\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041a.\u0410. \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0421\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0430. \u0411\u0438\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u044d\u043d\u0446\u0438\u043a\u043b\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044c. \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0430, \u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435, 2000\n*\u0412.\u0410\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0432. \u0415\u0432\u0440\u0435\u0438 \u0432 \u041a\u0413\u0411. \u041f\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0447\u0438 \u0438 \u0436\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0432\u044b. \u041c., \u042f\u0443\u0437\u0430 - \u042d\u043a\u0441\u043c\u043e, 2005.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pliner, Israel}}\n[[Category:1896 births]]\n[[Category:1939 deaths]]\n[[Category:Russian Jews]]\n[[Category:NKVD officers]]\n[[Category:Great Purge perpetrators]]\n[[Category:Great Purge victims from Russia]]\n[[Category:Jews executed by the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:People executed for treason against the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Russia]]\n[[Category:Soviet rehabilitations]]\n[[Category:Gulag governors]]\n\n\n{{russia-bio-stub}}\n\n[[ru:\u041f\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440, \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u044c \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2014}}\n[[File:Izrail Pliner NKVD.jpg|alt=Izrail Pliner|thumb|238x238px|Izrail Pliner]]\n'''Israel Pliner''' ({{lang-ru|\u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u044c \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041f\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440}}, '''Izrail Izrailevich Pliner''') (1896&ndash;1939) was a Soviet communist, high functionary of the [[Soviet secret police]], Jewish by origin. Notable posts include deputy chief of [[GULAG|GULAGS]]<ref>{{Cite book|last=Congdon|first=Lee|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=oK68DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT169&dq=Israel+Pliner&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=Israel%20Pliner&f=false|title=Solzhenitsyn: The Historical-Spiritual Destinies of Russia and the West|date=2017-09-15|publisher=Cornell University Press|isbn=978-1-60909-224-5|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Baberowski|first=J\u00f6rg|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=DqFTDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT148&dq=Israel+Pliner&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=Israel%20Pliner&f=false|title=Scorched Earth: Stalin's Reign of Terror|date=2016-11-22|publisher=Yale University Press|isbn=978-0-300-22057-5|language=en}}</ref> in (1935-1937) and  (1937-1938). \n\nHe was one of the main collaborators of [[Nikolai Yezhov]], head of the [[NKVD]] in the years 1936\u20131938, and collaborator of other organizers of the [[Great Purge|Great Terror in the USSR]]. \n\nOn August 16, 1937, he became the head of the board of the communist concentration camps GULAG [[NKVD]] five days after the beginning of [[Polish Operation of the NKVD]]. According to NKVD documents, 139,835 Poles who were citizens of the USSR were convicted in 1937. Of this number, 111 091 Poles were directly killed, and 28 744 Poles were sent to communist [[Gulag|GULAG]] concentration camps.\n\nIn 1937, he directed the deportation of 172,000 Korean citizens of the USSR from the Soviet Far East to Central Asia (to Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan).\n\nHe was arrested in 1938 and executed in 1939.<ref>[http://hrono.ru/biograf/bio_p/plinerii.php \"\u041f\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440 \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u044c \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447\"] at hrono.ru, citing books:\n\n*\u0417\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041a.\u0410. \u0418\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0421\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0430. \u0411\u0438\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u044d\u043d\u0446\u0438\u043a\u043b\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044c. \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0430, \u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435, 2000\n*\u0412.\u0410\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0432. \u0415\u0432\u0440\u0435\u0438 \u0432 \u041a\u0413\u0411. \u041f\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0447\u0438 \u0438 \u0436\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0432\u044b. \u041c., \u042f\u0443\u0437\u0430 - \u042d\u043a\u0441\u043c\u043e, 2005.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pliner, Israel}}\n[[Category:1896 births]]\n[[Category:1939 deaths]]\n[[Category:Russian Jews]]\n[[Category:NKVD officers]]\n[[Category:Great Purge perpetrators]]\n[[Category:Great Purge victims from Russia]]\n[[Category:Jews executed by the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:People executed for treason against the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Russia]]\n[[Category:Soviet rehabilitations]]\n[[Category:Gulag governors]]\n\n\n{{russia-bio-stub}}\n\n[[ru:\u041f\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0440, \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u044c \u0418\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447]]\n", "name_user": "Lovemankind83", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel_Pliner"}
